Capstone Project â€” Lists, Functions, and String Handling

Description

This project is a command-line task management system that allows users to register, add tasks, view tasks, and generate reports. It demonstrates the usage of lists, functions, and string handling in Python.

Table of Contents

Installation
Usage
Credits

INSTALLATION:

To install and run this project locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository to your local machine.
Navigate to the project directory.
Open a terminal or command prompt.
Run the Python script using the command python capstone_project.py.

USAGE:

After installing the project, you can use the following commands to interact with the task management system:

1.Register a New User (r): This command allows you to register a new user for the task management system.
2.Add a New Task (a): Use this command to add a new task to the system. You will be prompted to provide details such as the assigned user, task title, description, and due date.
3.View All Tasks (va): This command displays all tasks in a formatted manner, including the task title, assigned user, assigned date, due date, and task description.
4.View My Tasks (vm): Use this command to view tasks assigned to the current user. You can also mark tasks as completed or edit them.
5.Display Statistics (ds): This command displays statistics about the number of users and tasks in the system.
6.Generate a Report (gr): If you have admin access, you can generate reports summarising the tasks and users in separate files.

